\n{{CBB schedule entry\n| date         = March 12, 2020\n| time         = 6:00 pm\n| tv           = ESPN3\n| seed         = 1\n| neutral      = yes\n| oppseed      = 8\n| opponent     = Long Beach State\n| gamename     = Quarterfinals\n| w/l          = \n| score        = CANCELED\n| overtime     = \n| record       = 21\u201311\n| conference   = \n| highscorer   = &nbsp;\n| points       = \n| highrebounder= &nbsp;\n| rebounds     = \n| highassister = &nbsp;\n| assists      = \n| site_stadium = [[Honda Center]]\n| attend       = \n| site_cityst  = [[Anaheim, California|Anaheim, CA]]\n}}\n|-\n<ref>{{cite web |title=2019\u201320 Men's Basketball Schedule |url=https://ucirvinesports.com/schedule.aspx?path=mbball |publisher=[[University of California, Irvine]] |accessdate=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n{{CBB schedule end|region=|regionname=|notes=}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{UC Irvine Anteaters men's basketball navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2019-20 UC Irvine Anteaters Men's Basketball Team}}\n\n[[Category:UC Irvine Anteaters men's basketball seasons]]\n[[Category:2019 in sports in California|UC Irvine]]\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 Big West Conference men's basketball season|UC Irvine]]\n[[Category:2020 in sports in California|UC Irvine]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American college basketball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| sport = basketball\n| year = 2019\u201320\n| prev_year = 2018\u201319\n| next_year = 2020\u201321\n| team = UC Irvine Anteaters\n| logo = UC Irvine Anteaters logo.svg\n| logo_size = 100\n| conference = Big West Conference\n| short_conf = Big West\n| CoachRank = \n| APRank = \n| record = 21\u201311\n| conf_record = 13\u20133\n| wins_vacated = \n| ties_forfeited =\n| wins_forfeited = \n| conf_wins_vacated = \n| conf_wins_forfeited = \n| head_coach = [[Russell Turner (basketball)|Russell Turner]]\n| hc_year = 10th\n| asst_coach1 = [[Blaine Taylor]]\n| ac1_year = \n| asst_coach2 = Ryan Badrtalei\n| ac2_year = \n| asst_coach3 = Michael Wilder\n| ac3_year = \n| mvp = \n| mvp_year = \n| mvp2 = \n| mvp2_year = \n| captain = \n| captain_year = \n| captain2 = \n| captain2_year = \n| captain3 = \n| captain3_year = \n| captain4 = \n| captain4_year = \n| arena = [[Bren Events Center]]<br>(Capacity: 5,000)\n| champion = Big West regular season champions\n| tourney = \n| tourney_result = \n}}\n{{2019\u201320 Big West men's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2019\u201320 UC Irvine Anteaters men's basketball team''' represented the [[University of California, Irvine]] in the [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The Anteaters were led by tenth-year head coach [[Russell Turner (basketball)|Russell Turner]] competing in the [[Bren Events Center]]. UC Irvine is a member of the [[Big West Conference]]. The team won their 2nd straight Big West Regular Season title before the [[2020 Big West Conference Men's Basketball Tournament]] and subsequently, the remainder of the [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]] and postseason tournaments were canceled as a result of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|COVID-19 Pandemic]]. The team finished 21-11, and has won at least a share of 3 of the last 4 Big West Regular season titles. The program has won at least 20 games in 7 of the last 8 seasons. Turner became the winningest coach in program history on Jan 15 surpassing [[Pat Douglass]] total of 197 wins and won his 4th Big West Coach of the Year Award. Evan Leonard, Eyassu Worku, and Tommy Rutherford all recorded their 1000th point during the season, the first time the program has had 3 players score 1,000 career points in the same season. The team was 12th in the nation in FG % defense holding opponents to (38.8%) shooting, 11th in total rebounds (1,269), 3rd in rebounding margin (+9.4). Brad Greene pulled a Bren Events Center record 21 rebounds on Jan. 11 vs Hawai'i. <ref>{{cite web |title=2019-20 MEN'S BASKETBALL SEASON REVIEW  |url=https:https://ucirvinesports.com/news/2020/3/30/2019-20-mens-basketball-season-review.aspx |publisher=[[University of California, Irvine]] |accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Previous season==\n{{See also|2018\u201319 UC Irvine Anteaters men's basketball team}}\n\nThe Anteaters finished the season a program best 31\u20136 overall, and 15\u20131 in the conference and recorded their first ever NCAA Tournament win over [[2018\u201319 Kansas State Wildcats men's basketball team|Kansas State]] in the South Region 1st Round before falling to [[2018\u201319 Oregon Ducks men's basketball team|Oregon]] in the 2nd Round.<ref>{{cite web |title=Historic Season Comes to an End in NCAA Round of 32  |url=https://ucirvinesports.com/news/2019/3/24/mens-basketball-eaters-historic-season-comes-to-an-end-in-ncaa-round-of-32.aspx |publisher=[[University of California, Irvine]] |accessdate=25 March 2019}}</ref> During the season, the Anteaters participated in the 2019 [[Gulf Coast Showcase]], which was held in [[Estero, Florida]], where they were runner-ups defeating [[2018\u201319 UTSA Roadrunners men's basketball team|UTSA]] and [[2018\u201319 Tulane Green Wave men's basketball team|Tulane]] before losing to [[2018\u201319 Toledo Rockets men's basketball team|Toledo]]. Prior to the season, the Anteaters competed in the 2018 [[Asia-Pacific University Basketball Challenge]], hosted by the [[Korea Basketball Association|KBA]] and [[Yonsei University]] where they were also runner-ups. <ref>{{cite web |title=UCI FALLS TO RUSSIA, 92-91, AT THE ASIA PACIFIC UNIVERSITY CHALLENGE  |url=https://ucirvinesports.com/news/2018/8/12/mens-basketball-uci-falls-to-russia-92-91-at-the-asia-pacific-university-challenge.aspx?path=mbball |publisher=[[University of California, Irvine]] |accessdate=25 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Roster==\n\n{{CBB roster/Header|year=2019|team=UC Irvine Anteaters|teamcolors=y|sex=M|high_school=y}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=JC|last=Butler|dab=|num=0|pos=F|ft=6|in=5|lbs=200|class=So|rs=|cur_rs=|home=[[Racine, Wisconsin]]|high_school=